## Analysis and Description of the Main Target Image:

- **Count & Layers:** The structure is composed of a total of 17 blocks and has a maximum of 4 layers in the left part and 3 layers in the right part.

- **Spatial Relationships:** The structure is divided into two distinct parts: a taller structure on the left and a shorter structure on the right.

    - **Left Structure:**
        - **Layer 1 (Base):** Two yellow rectangular blocks (horizontal orientation) placed side-by-side.
        - **Layer 2:** Two orange cylindrical blocks placed on top of the yellow rectangular blocks, acting as pillars.
        - **Layer 3 (Platform):** One yellow rectangular block (horizontal orientation) placed on top of the cylindrical pillars, bridging them.
        - **Layer 4 (Roof):** A red rectangular block (horizontal orientation) is placed on the yellow platform, forming a base for the roof. Two orange triangular prism blocks are placed on top of the red rectangular block, forming a pointed roof.

    - **Right Structure:**
        - **Layer 1 (Base):** Three red arch blocks placed side-by-side in a row.
        - **Layer 2:** A yellow arch block is placed in the center on top of the red arches. A green rectangular block (vertical orientation) is placed to the right of the yellow arch, and a yellow rectangular block (vertical orientation) is placed to the left of the yellow arch.
        - **Layer 3 (Top):** A blue cube is placed on top of the yellow arch. A yellow rectangular block (vertical orientation) is placed on top of the green rectangular block. An orange cube is placed on top of the yellow rectangular block.
